cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE

This paper is about using deep learning algorithms to detect and classify malware by converting them into images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of vision-based deep learning algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the use of transfer learning and local interpretable model-agnostic explanation algorithm, which are techniques commonly used in cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the extraction of insights from the interpretation of the images, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper is focused on the validation of the interpretation fidelity, which could also be relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
